$interpreted: Roger: Apologies, this road is off limits. If you are in a hurry, tell your leader to come and negotiate with us.
Evil Merchant: Hoho~ the bandit with a big knife and no right arm. Looks like you're the legendary Roger we've heard so much about?

Roger: So, my reputation precedes me?
Then let's get to the point; only thing we want is the convoy's cargo.
Roger: As long as you behave yourselves and don't cause any trouble, none of you will be harmed. You have my word.
Evil Merchant: Hmph, I wonder who's going to be the one doing the harm.
Evil Merchant: Kingdom of the Sun has placed a hefty bounty on you. I'm going to make some extra profit on this business trip!

Roger: This is how many people you get to fight me?
Seems like you criminally underestimated my price.
Roger: Hmpf, that all you got?

Roger: Tie these folks up, 
then unload the cargo from the carts.
Roger: Jeff, patrol around the area to see if there are any villages that need relief. Take half of the supplies and distribute it to the villages.
Roger: The remaining half, we give some to the village in front of our camp...
Fearful Henchman: ... B, Boss Roger...
Fearful Henchman: I, if we do this... there won't be much left for us...
Roger: We are a small group anyway. The remaining supplies are plenty enough.
Fearful Henchman: ... I get it, it's just that...
Fearful Henchman: Since we help the village in front of our camp every time, there's no need to give so much every time, right?
Roger: Without them providing cover for us, we would've been busted by the kingdom army a long time ago. Moreover,
Roger: the village has experienced some bad harvest in the past few years. It makes sense that we repay them with some of our earnings.
Fearful Henchman: B... but, the other bros are starting to complain about this recently. Maybe this time we can...

Roger: Who is the boss right now! Me, or you? 
You think you're big enough to talk **** against me now?
Roger: Come on, speak up you stinkin brat!

Jeff: Roger, STOP! 
What the hell are you doing!?

Roger: Whew... take him away and treat his injuries.
Other people, keep moving the cargo, no more wasting time!
Jeff: Roger, are you alright? Seems you lose your temper easily these days.
Roger: No need to worry. I'm fine. Nothing's wrong.

Jeff: You're not fine at all...
Could it be the monster bite from way back...

Roger: Jeff, do NOT tell anyone about this;
especially Kittyeyes.
